properties.headline: High Surf Warning issued January 26 at 4:07AM HST until January 26 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF WARNING FOR NORTH AND WEST FACING SHORES OF NIIHAU
KAUAI OAHU MOLOKAI AND NORTH FACING SHORES OF MAUI...

...HIGH SURF ADVISORY FOR WEST FACING SHORES OF THE BIG ISLAND...

.The current large long-period northwest swell will hold through
this morning, then gradually lower this afternoon through
Tuesday. Another large northwest swell is expected on Wednesday
and will likely bring advisory level surf along exposed north and
west facing shores.

* WHAT...Surf of 20 to 30 feet this morning, lowering to 18 to 25
feet this afternoon along north and west facing shores of Niihau
and Kauai, and north facing shores of Oahu, Molokai and Maui.
Along west facing shores of Oahu and Molokai, surf of 16 to 22
feet this morning, lowering to 12 to 20 feet.

* WHERE...North and west facing shores of Niihau, Kauai, Oahu,
Molokai and north facing shores of Maui.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM HST this evening.

* IMPACTS...High. Expect ocean water occasionally sweeping
across portions of beaches, very strong breaking waves, and
strong longshore and rip currents. Breaking waves may
occasionally impact harbors making navigating the harbor
channel dangerous.
properties.instruction:
Large, breaking surf, significant shorebreak, and dangerous
currents make entering the water very hazardous.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST THIS EVENING
